TECH_PARAM_3.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Surface pressure recorded just before the previous descent but data is corrected on board the float. Note: cumulative NEGATIVE offset (real offset * -1) but no further correction required. Autocorrected

TECH_PARAM_5.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: battery voltage during inactive surface phase

TECH_PARAM_8.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Firmware version of the sensor board.

TECH_PARAM_9.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: SIM card number of the float.

TECH_PARAM_10.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Oil volume transferred from the external bladder during the descent to park (between the surface and the second threshold of the buoyancy reduction phase). This is the oil volume tranferred  during the NUMBER_ValveActionsAtSurfaceDuringDescent_COUNT valve actions.

TECH_PARAM_11.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of solenoid valve actions at the surface until the crossing of the GAP threshold

TECH_PARAM_12.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Oil volume transferred from the external bladder during the descent to park (between the second threshold of the buoyancy reduction phase and the end of the descent to park). This is the oil volume tranferred  during the NUMBER_ValveActionsDuringDescentToPark_COUNT valve actions.

TECH_PARAM_13.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of valve actions between the crossing  of the gap threshold and the end of descent at park pressure

TECH_PARAM_14.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Time when the float escaped from grounding.

TECH_PARAM_15.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Oil volume, transferred to the external bladder, needed to leave the sea bottom when grounded.

TECH_PARAM_16.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of valve actions during park phase

TECH_PARAM_17.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of pump actions while at park depth

TECH_PARAM_18.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: drift at park pressure: number of entries in margin around park pressure target - specifically, how many times the float enters the band of pressure surrounding the target park pressure (generally +/- 30db)

TECH_PARAM_19.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: drift at park pressure: number of exits from margin around park pressure target - specifically, how many times the float exits the band of pressure surrounding the target park pressure (generally +/- 30db)

TECH_PARAM_20.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Time when the float stabilized at parking depth (improved stabilization needed for some Bio sensors).

TECH_PARAM_21.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Pressure of the float when stabilized at parking depth (improved stabilization needed for some Bio sensors).

TECH_PARAM_22.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Oil volume transferred from the external bladder during the descent to start profile pressure. This is the oil volume tranferred  during the NUMBER_ValveActionsDuringDescentToProfile_COUNT valve actions.

TECH_PARAM_23.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of valve actions during descent to start profile pressure

TECH_PARAM_24.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Oil volume transferred to the external bladder during the ascent to surface This is the oil volume tranferred  during the NUMBER_PumpActionsDuringAscentToSurface_COUNT pump actions.

TECH_PARAM_25.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of pump actions between start and end of ascent

TECH_PARAM_26.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of pump actions needed to start the ascent.

TECH_PARAM_27.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Slow ascent start time (the upper part of the ascent can be performed with a lower vertical speed).

TECH_PARAM_28.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Oil volume transferred to the external bladder during the slow ascent to surface. This is the oil volume tranferred  during the NUMBER_PumpActionsDuringSlowAscentToSurface_COUNT pump actions.

TECH_PARAM_29.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of pump actions between slow ascent start and end of ascent.

TECH_PARAM_30.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Resumed ascent start time (the float can stop the ascent to perform a ice cover detection and resume the profile if no ice is detected).

TECH_PARAM_31.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Oil volume transferred to the external bladder during the resumed ascent to surface. This is the oil volume tranferred  during the NUMBER_PumpActionsDuringResumedAscentToSurface_COUNT pump actions.

TECH_PARAM_32.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of pump actions between resumed ascent start and end of ascent.

TECH_PARAM_33.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of valve actions during park phase

TECH_PARAM_34.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of pump actions while at park depth

TECH_PARAM_35.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: drift at park pressure: number of entries in margin around park pressure target - specifically, how many times the float enters the band of pressure surrounding the target park pressure (generally +/- 30db)

TECH_PARAM_36.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: drift at park pressure: number of exits from margin around park pressure target - specifically, how many times the float exits the band of pressure surrounding the target park pressure (generally +/- 30db)

TECH_PARAM_37.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Pressure switch activation time (the float detected an empty internal reservoir).

TECH_PARAM_38.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Total size of the files sent during the previous Iridium RUDICS session.

TECH_PARAM_39.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of files sent during the previous Iridium RUDICS session.

TECH_PARAM_40.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Mean output flow rate to send files of the previous Iridium RUDICS session.

TECH_PARAM_41.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Iridium session needed to send files during the previous Iridium RUDICS session.

TECH_PARAM_42.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of remote control commands successfully considered.

TECH_PARAM_43.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of remote control commands rejected by the float.

TECH_PARAM_44.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of remote control commands not recognised by the float (for example because they concern unknown parameters).

TECH_PARAM_45.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: A new configuration for the sensor board has been received.

TECH_PARAM_46.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: A new configuration script file has been received.

TECH_PARAM_48.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Ratio between float activity and stand bye during the cycle.

TECH_PARAM_49.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Total duration of valve actions during the cycle.

TECH_PARAM_50.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Total duration of pump actions during the cycle.

TECH_PARAM_51.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Total duration of CTD activity during the cycle.

TECH_PARAM_52.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: duration of the previous iridium session

TECH_PARAM_53.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Total duration of GPS activity during the cycle.

TECH_PARAM_55.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm raised in case of inconsistency in the configuration

TECH_PARAM_56.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm raised when the float sinks without any valve actions.

TECH_PARAM_57.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm raised when the float doesn't sink even with valve actions.

TECH_PARAM_58.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Liste des defaults (FRAM, FLASH, RTC, Vbatt, Pi, Pe, SBE41-Cutoff, SBE41-Offset, GPS, Payload, Sensor(xxx), Transmitter)
TECH_PARAM_58.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Auto-test is performed at the beginning of the mission: Flag 0 = Problem, 1 = OK)

TECH_PARAM_59.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: The failed flag bits (1 if failed, 0 otherwise) set during the initial check are provided in reverse order for: FRAM, FLASH, RTC, Vbatt, Pi, Pe, SBE41-Cutoff, SBE41-Offset, GPS, Payload, Sensor, Transmitter (see float manual for details).

TECH_PARAM_60.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm raised when a low level of the battery is detected (the check is done without any load on the battery).

TECH_PARAM_61.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm raised when a low level of the battery is detected (the check is done with load on the battery, i.e. pump action at depth).

TECH_PARAM_62.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm raised when external pressure is too low.

TECH_PARAM_63.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm raised when external pressure is too high.

TECH_PARAM_64.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm raised when the external pressure sensor reports abnormal number of successive errors.

TECH_PARAM_65.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm raised when internal pressure is too high.

TECH_PARAM_66.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm when water is detected inside one of the sensors.

TECH_PARAM_67.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm raised when the float is hanged during ascent.

TECH_PARAM_68.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm raised when the descent speed is too high and the float brakes.

TECH_PARAM_69.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm raised when the system fails.

TECH_PARAM_70.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm raised when the payload card fails.

TECH_PARAM_71.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm raised when the GPS fails.

TECH_PARAM_72.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm raised when the hydraulic engine fails.

TECH_PARAM_73.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm raised when the Analog to Digital Converter fails.

TECH_PARAM_74.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm raised when a file cannot be transmitted.

TECH_PARAM_75.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm raised when the Real Time Clock fails.

TECH_PARAM_76.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm raised when the pressure switch fails.

TECH_PARAM_77.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm raised when the float switches to the End Of Life mode. When reported as a NUMBER, it provides the reason of the End Of Life (see float manual for details).

TECH_PARAM_78.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm raised the float ascends in an emergency mode.

TECH_PARAM_79.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm raised when a feedback occurs.

TECH_PARAM_80.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm raised when the float is hanged during ascent.

TECH_PARAM_81.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm raised when the float escaped from hanging during ascent.

TECH_PARAM_83.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: test message data reporting pressure at the surface during drift - cycle 0

TECH_PARAM_84.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm raised when the descent speed is too high and the float brakes.

TECH_PARAM_85.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm raised when the descent speed is too high and the float brakes.

TECH_PARAM_86.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Time of ice detection by the ISA algorithm.

TECH_PARAM_89.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Alarm raised when the float switches to the End Of Life mode. When reported as a NUMBER, it provides the reason of the End Of Life (see float manual for details).
